Hey Shineola breath, it is phyicaly impossiable to get lawn mowers to fly any higher than four feet. This even include the nuclear dual engine turbo power lawn mowers.  Flying device like these were mostly used in the delta country in the early years of the war.  Big papa Son gook in Siagon stopped them all and had them grounded because those fixed wing reject pilots (whirly bird types) were mowing down all the rice crops.  Made the VC recruiters job real easy you know and it helped to prolong the war.  To this date no one has ever confessed to have piloted a lawn mower in Nam.  <br><br>
